    {
      "cadence": "weekly",
      "description": "Camera and screen-share if remote. He drives, you observe and ask.\nWatch the meta-moves \u2014 when he hits something unexpected, what's the\n*first* thing he does? Which tool? Reproduce in isolation? Check logs\nat a particular layer? These habits are mostly invisible to him; the\nfastest way to skill transfer is copying them.\n\nWithin 24 hours, write up what you saw \u2014 observations, not instructions.\n\"When he saw the failing test, he ran X first instead of Y. Why?\"\nThese notes are the most concentrated learning material you'll generate.\n\nGoal by month 12: predict his next move during the session.\nGoal by month 24: open PRs to the codebase yourself.\n",
      "due": "today at 19:00",
      "fires": true,
      "id": "weekly-pair-with-engineer",
      "labels": [
        "active-practice"
      ],
      "syllabus_key": "long-way",
